Subject: [control-bot] Disable ConversationEnhancer follow-up buttons in classic mode

claude-code-telegram v1.6.0 hardcodes the ConversationEnhancer to load whenever
`agentic_mode` is false (classic mode). It has NO env flag — `ENABLE_CONVERSATION_MODE`
appears in the upstream .env.example but is not a Settings field, so it is silently
ignored. The enhancer appends a "💡 What would you like to do next?" inline keyboard
(Add tests / Review / Continue Coding / End Session …) after every Claude reply, which
is noise for our single-purpose pipeline bot.

This patch gates the feature off so it never loads. Apply during the Phase-7 image
build, after installing the bot, e.g.:

  PKG=$(python -c "import src.bot.features.registry as r, os; print(os.path.dirname(r.__file__))")
  patch -p1 -d "$PKG/../.." < control-bot/patches/0001-disable-conversation-enhancer.patch

(Adjust -d to the site-packages root so the a/src/... path resolves. Verify with:
the startup log must show `enabled_features` WITHOUT "conversation".)

Regenerated 2026-07-12 against the installed claude-code-telegram@v1.6.0 source tree (context/line-numbers corrected; the -/+ transformation is unchanged).

--- a/src/bot/features/registry.py
+++ b/src/bot/features/registry.py
@@ -91,8 +91,11 @@
             except Exception as e:
                 logger.error("Failed to initialize voice handler", error=str(e))
 
-        # Conversation enhancements - skip in agentic mode
-        if not self.config.agentic_mode:
+        # Conversation enhancements - DISABLED for the locked control-bot profile.
+        # v1.6.0 has no env flag for this (ENABLE_CONVERSATION_MODE is not a Settings
+        # field), so it is patched off here to suppress the "What would you like to do
+        # next?" follow-up suggestion buttons after every pipeline reply.
+        if False and not self.config.agentic_mode:
             try:
                 self.features["conversation"] = ConversationEnhancer()
                 logger.info("Conversation enhancer feature enabled")
